Password Policy

This policy sets guidelines for creating, changing, and storing passwords to ensure the security of sensitive data. All users should ensure that their passwords: 

• Comprised of 8-12 characters, including upper and lowercase letters, numbers, and special characters 
• Are changed every 90 days 
• Are not easy to guess, based on personal information (names, birth dates, etc)
• Are stored securely and not shared with anyone
• Do not contain any complete words 

It is the responsibility of all users to protect their passwords and to adhere to this policy. Any users who fail to comply with this policy may be subject to disciplinary action.
